ning them, this book will empower local authority workers, policy-makers and researchers, and anyone interested in social justice, to challenge damaging, aggressive neoliberal statecraft.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFamily policyzGreat Britain. 0aPoor familiesxServices forzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831111966640 cprintz978144733474340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447334736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447334736/original  a978-3-11-119666-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles